<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>shouting head • talking head</xh5><p> <i>shouting head</i>—(derog., also: barking head) a television commentator who speaks in a loud voice and whose comments tend to be aggressive: We have instead <u>shouting heads</u> trying to interrupt each other to get their talking points across.</p><p> <i>talking head—</i>a television commentator whose upper body is all that is shown on the screen: Former TV <u>talking head</u> Jim Compton did not respond to the Weekly’s request for an interview.</p> </entry>
